    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-24T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-24T07:00:00-05:00" n="156"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d156">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/9186: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Special Representative</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HCEM1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">House</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-24T12:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 24, 1918—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received November 24—9:20
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>159. Secret for the President. Your number 59, November 22, 5 p.m. It will be
                    unnecessary for you to bring any domestic servants with you except your valet
                    and Mrs. <persName corresp="#p_WW1">Wilson</persName>’s maid.</p>
                <p>I shall take up the matter of the use of English at the conference with the
                    British and hope to secure their support. I am working to secure a definite
                    agreement from the British and French that England, France, Italy and the United
                    States should each have five places at the table, [in line with my] suggestion
                    contained in my number 7 and accepted by you in your number 10.<note n="27"
                        xml:id="d156fn27">No. 7 is printed on <ref target="#pg_156">p. 156</ref>;
                        No. 10, on <ref target="#pg_157">p. 157</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Thank you so much for your message of sympathy. I am still in bed and very weak
                    but making satisfactory progress.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward House</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
